        <td vAlign="top" width="932"><h2>What are Installment Payments?</h2>
            You have the option to pay your fees and dues in 3 installment payments. Installment payments can only be made using a credit card account. A $25 service fee will be equally divided among the three payments. Once you select this option, you will see the payment amounts and dates to be paid (based on your election date).<br><br>

            If you fail to make the second or third payments, your account will be put on hold and you will not be able to make new or use your booked reservations. You will have 7 calendar days to provide an alternative payment method online. <br><br>
            
            If a successful alternative payment is not made within 7 calendar days, you will no longer qualify for an installment plan, your account will become delinquent and appropriate late fees will be applied based on the original due date and actual default date.<br><br>
            
            <b>Premier Owners:</b> You will need to arrange all payments using Points before initiating an installment plan. Once you are on an installment plan, you can no longer elect to use Points to pay your fees.<br><br>
            
           <b> Encore Rewards:</b> You will need to arrange all payments using Rewards before initiating an installment plan. Once you are on an installment plan, you can no longer elect to use Rewards to pay your fees.<br><br>
